<h1 align="center"><font size="7" face="Arial">How to make good metrics?</font></h1>
  <p align="center"><![if !vml]><span style='mso-ignore:vglayout;position:
absolute;z-index:0;left:1134px;top:65px;width:26px;height:26px'>
  <img src="intro_files/image002.gif" v:shapes="_x0000_s1026"></span><![endif]></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal">　</p>
  <p class="MsoNormal">　</p>
  <p><b><font face="Arial" size="6">1. What do you hope to accomplish?</font></b></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: .5in"><font face="Arial" size="6">
  Though metrics should play descriptive role rather than prescriptive one, it 
  does affect how people behave. </font></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: .5in"><font face="Arial" size="6">
  SLOC or Labor hours</font></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: .5in">　</p>
  <p><b><font face="Arial" size="6">2. What data do you have readily available?</font></b></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: .5in"><font face="Arial" size="6">
  Make use of those routinely collected data and suppress the additional time to 
  collect, collate, analyze and present.</font></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: .5in"><font face="Arial" size="6">
  Counts of problem reports, SLOC</font></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: .5in">　</p>
  <p><b><font face="Arial" size="6">3. </font>
  <font face="Brush Script MT" size="7">&nbsp;<img border="0" src="kiss.gif" width="116" height="90"> 
  Kiss !</font></b></p>
  <p>　</p>
  <p><b><font face="Arial" size="6">4. Do a sanity check</font></b></p>
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: .5in"><font face="Arial" size="6">Do 
  not trust those sources that people can easily manipulate, such as timestamp. 
   </font></p>
  
